@node Main "Main"

    Welcome to Guided!

(see history for changes since last prerelease)

Ok.. This is not really a realease of the program,
it's only a very internal version, but because I
came to the point in the developing where quite
some effort needs to be put into the project, and
I have other things to prioritize, I decided to
release what I made so far to see if there's any
interest out there for me to keep on development.

So if you would like to see a finnished product, 
encourage me! 
The program is working, though, I use it myself
all the time!

For obvious reasons, the documentation is very bad
too at this point, actually it lacks any kind of
needful information. 

As it is now, the program just keeps your different
nodes seperated and keep track of node and guide tags.
When I make the real guide editor class, it will
also display the guide something like wysiwyg,
etc blah blah.

It's still fully ok to send me bugreports, ideas
and comments!

/Linus




Guided is a small editor made specially to create
AmigaGuide documents.
At the moment, there is not much more functionallity
than a normal texteditor, except that it keeps tracks
of some tags for you, but hopefully, if there is any
interest, this will improve with further versions.

